      • updateScreen

        public void updateScreen​(ScreenController controller)
        Description copied from interface: Displayable
        Required to transfer the action to the ScreenController. The screen controller should implement a method to itself handle the event. Typical usage could be : 

         public void updateScreen(ScreenController controller) {
     controller.updateSelection(this);
 }
        where updateSelection() does the heavy update work.
        Parameters:
        controller - the screen controller used to dispatch event.

      • accept

        public void accept​(UmlVisitor visitor)
        Description copied from interface: UmlVisitorElement
        This method is used to redirect the operations to be completed upon visiting to the corresponding method in UmlVisitor. Basic implementation should look like : 
             public void accept(UmlVisitor visitor) {
         visitor.visit(this);
     }
        As such, the appropriate method in the UmlVisitor will be called
        Parameters:
        visitor - the visitor on which the operation to be performered is defined.
